modules.description: This module provides low-level operations for manipulating BPF headers (e.g., timestamp, length fields) and managing socket-based packet capture with DHCP filters and platform-specific drivers. It works directly with `Cstruct.t` buffers for memory-efficient splitting and processing of binary data, such as network packets. Use cases include network monitoring, packet analysis, and systems requiring direct interaction with raw packet buffers or platform-specific capture mechanisms.

This module enables low-level network packet manipulation by providing functions to open and manage raw network links, read and send Ethernet frames, and apply BPF filters. It operates on raw network interfaces and works with `Cstruct.t` buffers for packet data. Concrete use cases include crafting and injecting custom Ethernet frames, implementing DHCP clients or servers, and capturing specific network traffic such as filtering and responding to DHCP requests.
